<TR>
<TD COLSPAN=3><HR SIZE=4>
<FONT SIZE=2>Mt. McKinley is the tallest mountain in North America -- Native Alaskans know it as "Denali". In this remote Alaskan wilderness, our self-reliant expedition will climb Denali via the Muldrow Glacier route on the north side. The route from Muldrow Glacier to Karsten's Ridge treks across tundra and the McKinley River, and 
climbs to the Harper Glacier. On Harper Glacier, we usually set up high camp for a summit attempt. Look forward to severe weather, extreme conditions, and technical terrain.
<HR SIZE=4>
</TD>
</TR>

